1766588 24 2 Appointment of Executive Officer.-
1710857 1For every cantonment there shall be an Executive Officer appointed by the Central Government or by such person as the Central Government may authorise in this behalf: Provided that the Board may empower any of its members or officers to exercise or perform in the absence of the Executive Officer from the cantonment all or any of such powers or duties of an Executive Officer under this Act as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.
Explanation.-- In this proviso, the word" officers" shall mean any of the supervisory staff of the Board as may be specified by the Board.
238089 2Not less than one- half of the cost of the salary of the Executive Officer shall be paid by the Central Government and the balance from the cantonment fund.
1856743 3The Executive Officer shall be the Secretary of the Board and of every Committee of the Board and may participate in every meeting of the Board and of every Committee of the board but, shall not be a member of the Board or of any such Committee.
1750422 24A Duties of Executive Officer.- Subject to the provisions of clause (b) and clause (d) of sub- section
564539 1of section 22, the Executive Officer shall--
577771 aexercise all the powers and perform all the duties conferred or imposed upon him by or under this Act or any other law for the time being in force;
1472655 bprescribe the duties of, and exercise supervision and control over the acts and proceedings of, officers and other employees of the Board, other than medical officer in charge of the cantonment general hospital or dispensary;
602319 cbe responsible for the custody of all records of the Board;
1457276 darrange for the performance of such duties relative to the proceedings of the Board or of any Committee of the Board or of any Committee of Arbitration constituted under this Act, as those bodies may respectively impose on him;
339721 ecomply with every requisition of the Board on any matter pertaining to the administration of the cantonment.]
